ckModal_main_2531410\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qsq1665702923854.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qsq1665702923854.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qsq1665702923854.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qsq1665702923854\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Increasing Virtual Memory on Windows\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface can take advantage of extra memory on Windows systems that have 1 GB or more of physical memory available.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__context_w1472ab1b5b1_w1473ab1b5_w1474ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__topic_d46343e1_d46344e1_d46345e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__p_d46346e1_d46347e1_d46348e1\">On 64-bit systems, Uniface can automatically claim up to 4 GB of extra virtual memory.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__p_d46349e1_d46350e1_d46351e1\">On 32-bit Windows platforms, you need to enable Windows' RAM tuning feature:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__li_d23093e1_d23094e1_d23095e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__p_d46352e1_d46353e1_d46354e1\">Set the Windows <code class=\"ph codeph\">/3GB</code> startup parameter in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">boot.ini</span> file.\n For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">multi(0)disk(0)rdisk(0)partition(1)/WIN7=\"Microsoft Windows 7 Professional\" /noexecute=optin /fastdetect /3GB</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__li_d23096e1_d23097e1_d23098e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Restart the Windows.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__result_w1475ab1b5b5_w1476ab1b5_w1477ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv result\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__topic_d46355e1_d46356e1_d46357e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__p_d46358e1_d46359e1_d46360e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">/3GB</code> parameter changes the way\n               Windows allocates its 4 GB of virtual address space, enlarging the memory available\n               to user applications to 3 GB, and reducing the memory available to kernel-mode\n               components to the remaining 1 GB.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qsq1665702923854__p_d46361e1_d46362e1_d46363e1\">For applications that do not use much memory, this\n               parameter makes no difference, but it can be helpful for applications that often run\n               out of memory (Uniface message).</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">\"Cannot claim more memory\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531410\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531410\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Increasing Virtual Memory on Windows Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Increasing Virtual Memory on Windows Uniface can take advantage of extra memory on Windows systems that have 1 GB or more of physical memory available. On 64-bit systems, Uniface can automatically claim up to 4 GB of extra virtual memory. On 32-bit Windows platforms, you need to enable Windows' RAM tuning feature: Set the Windows /3GB startup parameter in the boot.ini file. For example: multi(0)disk(0)rdisk(0)partition(1)/WIN7=\"Microsoft Windows 7 Professional\" /noexecute=optin /fastdetect /3GB Copy Restart the Windows. The /3GB parameter changes the way Windows allocates its 4 GB of virtual address space, enlarging the memory available to user applications to 3 GB, and reducing the memory available to kernel-mode components to the remaining 1 GB. For applications that do not use much memory, this parameter makes no difference, but it can be helpful for applications that often run out of memory (Uniface message). \"Cannot claim more memory\" Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}